review_text: Amazing park. Family friendly. The heartbeat of the neighborhood.
A bit muddy & crowded. But overall it's a nice park for kids 2-12. No swings.
Nice shaded park to spend some time in the playground or just hanging out in a hammock.
Nice temporary ice skating rink up right now. 5-year-old loves the play equipment in the nice gated area.

(Translated by Google) Park offering a full range of street furniture and an island of shade on hot summer days! Parking without vignette available, green oasis at no cost for neighborhood residents. I who live in the countryside, I compare the noise level of the park with the schoolyard in my village, during recess !!!
